ers": {"type": "object", "properties": {"plan": {"description": "Markdown text describing the step-by-step plan (bullet list).", "title": "Plan", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["plan"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "check_progress", "description": "Log a progress note and return a JSON snapshot of deliverables + plan excerpt.\n\nAppends `<UTC ISO timestamp> <note>` to `workspace/.progress.log`, then\nreturns a JSON string containing:\n  - `output_files`: list of {name, size_bytes} under `workspace/output/`.\n  - `success_artifact_present`: whether the task's success artifact glob matches.\n  - `plan_excerpt`: first 1000 chars of `.plan.md` (or empty if missing).\n  - `note_count`: total notes logged so far.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"note": {"description": "Short progress note to append to the log (plain text, one line).", "title": "Note", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["note"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "submit_done", "description": "End the episode. Set success=true only if criteria met (agent-declared).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"success": {"description": "Whether the agent believes the task objective is satisfied.", "title": "Success", "type": "boolean"}, "summary": {"default": "", "description": "Short optional note for logging.", "title": "Summary", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["success"]}}}], "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `spilterlize_limma_rbe`\n\n# Real R-task: spilterlize_limma_rbe\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `epigen-spilterlize_integrate-finish` (family: `rna`, stage: `late`, difficulty: `3`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given `input/normalized.csv` (gene \u00d7 sample log-scale data) and\n`input/annotation.csv` (sample \u00d7 `group, batch`). Call\n`limma::removeBatchEffect(as.matrix(data), batch=annot$batch,\ndesign=model.matrix(~group, annot))` and write to\n`output/integrated_data.csv` via `data.table::fwrite(..., row.names=TRUE)`.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/integrated_data.csv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: integrated_data.csv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"annotation.csv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"annotation.csv\"\n    },\n    \"normalized.csv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"normalized.csv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/integrated_data.csv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_Xdzvo4FrXc3jkGyOCStEippg", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary R libraries: `limma` and `data.table`.\\n2. Read the input files `input/normalized.csv` and `input/annotation.csv` using `fread` from the `data.table` package.\\n3. Convert the gene expression data to a matrix format suitable for `removeBatchEffect`.\\n4. Create a design matrix using the `group` column from the annotation data.\\n5. Use `limma::removeBatchEffect` to adjust the gene expression data for batch effects.\\n6. Write the corrected data to `output/integrated_data.csv` using `fwrite`, ensuring row names are preserved.\\n7. Verify the output file exists and submit the task as complete.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (609 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_Xdzvo4FrXc3jkGyOCStEippg"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "c