ies: `limma` and `data.table`.\\n2. Read the input files `input/normalized.csv` and `input/annotation.csv` using `fread` from the `data.table` package.\\n3. Convert the gene expression data to a matrix format suitable for `removeBatchEffect`.\\n4. Create a design matrix using the `group` column from the annotation data.\\n5. Use `limma::removeBatchEffect` to adjust the gene expression data for batch effects.\\n6. Write the corrected data to `output/integrated_data.csv` using `fwrite`, ensuring row names are preserved.\\n7. Verify the output file exists and submit the task as complete.\\n\\n**Note:** Ensure that the data matrix is numeric and does not contain any non-numeric values or row names that might interfere with the `removeBatchEffect` function.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (776 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_ZvP79SjqcVXyWeCi5Nys59c4"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_NlT25puuNLo10PFzEsqlfS9e", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(limma)\\nlibrary(data.table)\\ndata <- fread('input/normalized.csv', data.table=FALSE)\\nannot <- fread('input/annotation.csv', data.table=FALSE)\\nrownames(data) <- data[, 1]\\ndata_matrix <- as.matrix(data[, -1])\\ndesign <- model.matrix(~group, data=annot)\\ncorrected_data <- removeBatchEffect(data_matrix, batch=annot$batch, design=design)\\nfwrite(as.data.frame(corrected_data), 'output/integrated_data.csv', row.names=TRUE)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}], "hide_old_env_states": false, "hide_old_action_content": false}, "next_agent_state": {"tools": [{"type": "function", "info": {"name": "run_shell", "description": "Run a shell command in the task work_dir (bash -lc).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"command": {"description": "Shell command string passed to `bash -lc`.", "title": "Command", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["command"]}}}, {"type": "fu